{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c113c462-9af6-482d-98db-9deda5a455d2","content":"No pipeline files found in this repo, so here's general guidance:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your test project** — add to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n```\n\n**2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** in your pipeline:\n\n```yaml\n# Before:\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After:\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: always()\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n  condition: always()\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n- Tests run via `dotnet test` instead of the VSTest runner\n- TRX output is requested explicitly with `--logger trx`\n- `PublishTestResults@2` replaces the built-in reporting from VSTest@3\n- Code coverage is collected via `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` and published separately\n- Use `condition: always()` so results publish even on test failures","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d6ee1cc7-230c-4327-ac01-7e57348cad6b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant files. This is a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":490,"requestId":"CFE6:21A8FE:61AB03D:6CDACF7:69EC0EEC"},"id":"145ed21e-8590-428c-85a3-d0fa0858e4ab","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:45.989Z","parentId":"0518cbf7-57ca-4b24-9e43-2d10128ebb27"}
